  "text": "In this part we describe the methods to use the scripts which allow to make a prediction on the orientation and position of the division axis. This prediction will have as inputs 3D cell shapes defined following the preceding paragraphs, and parameters, which relate to the distribution of astral microtubule (MT) forces within cells, and to simulation procedures. As such, it is important to state that those model can solely be useful to study cell division in cell types and systems in which MTs are prime contributor of nuclei/spindle position, as in most vertebrate and invertebrate early embryos [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In our model, MT forces may depend on the spatial distribution of MTs around centrosomes, the length of MTs, or the presence of cortical domains.",
